item.title: Thousands join NT home maintenance scheme
item.description: Almost 20,000 Northern Territory home owners have applied for improvement and maintenance grants to help keep tradies in work during the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Battling anxiety in the age of COVID-19
item.description: As the world retreats indoors, people living with obsessive compulsive disorder are fighting a battle on two fronts.

item.title: Thousands of airport staff facing the sack
item.description: Thousands of airport goundstaff are facing the sack as the coronavirus pandemic suffocates the aviation industry.

item.title: Another day of no new virus cases in WA
item.description: No new cases of coronavirus have been confirmed in Western Australia for the second time in three days and eight more patients have recovered.

item.title: China’s Dutton attack unhelpful: treasurer
item.description: Treasurer Josh Frydenberg has hit back at China's attack on Home Affairs Minister Peter Dutton after he was accused of parroting US lines.

item.title: Call for more research on virus spread
item.description: An Australian researcher fears the world could be falling behind in efforts to understand how coronavirus spreads as it races to find a vaccine.

item.title: Youths clash with police in Paris
item.description: Youths have clashed with police overnight in suburbs around Paris, Le Point website and Agence France Presse report, the latest outbreak of trouble as strict lockdown rules to tackle the coronavirus heighten social tensions.

item.title: New COVID-19 death in New Zealand
item.description: New Zealand's coronavirus toll is now at 14 after the death of an elderly woman in the South Island.

item.title: Australia to start strategic fuel reserve
item.description: Australia will establish a strategic fuel reserve to safeguard supplies in times of crisis as the federal government seizes on record low oil prices.

item.title: Hong Kong reshuffles government
item.description: China's state council has approved a Hong Kong government shake-up at a time when Beijing is reaffirming its authority over the city, raising political tensions and risking a revival of anti-government protests after months of relative calm.
